original: Lutteman, Sven Erik, borgmästare, Norrköping, f. 15/11/02 i Sthlm av sjökapt. Carl Edvard L. o. Ida Matilda Stehn. G. 30 m. Marianne Ahl-berg. — Studrex. v. nya elemrsk. i Sthlm 21, jur. kand. v. Sthlms högsk. 25. E. o. not. i Göta hovr. 25, tings-tjg. i Hall. södra doms. 25-28, tf. stadsnot. i Halmstad 29, v. assessor i Norrköp. s. å., assessor där 32, rådman 47, borgmäst. 47. Ordf. i skatteavskriv-n rkomm., taxrnd o. pens rnd, led. av länsprövn rnd, allm. omb. h. Norrköp. stadshypoteksfören. o. bostadskredit-fören., ordf. i samibeskattn rsakk., led. av styr. f. ett flert. ideella fören. m. m.
translated: Lutteman, Sven Erik, mayor, Norrköping, born on 15/11/02 in Stockholm to Captain Carl Edvard L. and Ida Matilda Stehn. Married in 1930 to Marianne Ahlberg. Studied at the new elementary school in Stockholm until 1921, received a law degree from Stockholm University in 1925. Served as a trainee and deputy notary in the Göta Court of Appeal in 1925, as a court clerk in the Halland South District Court from 1925-1928, as an acting notary in Halmstad in 1929, as an assessor in Norrköping from the same year, as an assessor there in 1932, as a magistrate in 1947, and as a mayor in 1947. He served as chairman of the tax depreciation committee, the tax assessment committee, and the pension committee, and was a member of the county examination board. Additionally, he was a general representative of the Norrköping Mortgage Association and the Housing Credit Association, chairman of the joint taxation investigation, and a member of the board of several nonprofit associations, among other things.
